  "summary": "### \ud83d\udc65 LAYPERSON TRANSLATION\nImagine a store with almost empty shelves, and customers getting frustrated because they can't buy what they need. We fixed this by getting more products into the store, getting them there faster, and making sure they arrive more often.\n\n### \ud83d\udcc8 BUSINESS ANALYSIS\nThe executed actions yielded a significant return on investment by reducing stockout probability to 0%, minimizing customer complaints, and optimizing stock levels, thereby ensuring a substantial reduction in potential losses and an improvement in overall customer satisfaction. The approved cashflow impact of -PKR 450,000 was a strategic investment in constraint compliance and risk reduction.\n\n### \ud83d\udd0d CRITICAL OVERVIEW\nThe conflict scenario presented a critical stock level of 3,200 units, with a high stockout probability of 91% and 23 active customer complaints. To mitigate this, actions were executed to optimize stock levels, reduce supplier lead time, and increase delivery frequency. The outcome resulted in an optimal stock level of 11,200 units, a reduced supplier lead time of 7 days, and a significant decrease in customer complaints. The overall resolution led to a substantial reduction in stockout probability and a notable improvement in cashflow impact.",
